You could have it in vi edit mode, just do:
bindkey -vs 'cpfl' 'cp _!\^ _!$'

This is one of the things I really dig about zsh: how we can rebind stuff.
I have my zsh set up like my vim setup so that if I press jj it will go from
insert mode to command mode.

The function is probably better though anyway.

-fREW

